docs.abstract: No issue united Democrats in the 2018 campaign as much as protecting the Affordable Care Act’s guaranteed insurance coverage of people with pre-existing conditions.
docs.snippet: No issue united Democrats in the 2018 campaign as much as protecting the Affordable Care Act’s guaranteed insurance coverage of people with pre-existing conditions.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats, claiming a mandate from voters, opened a legislative campaign on Wednesday to secure protections under the Affordable Care Act for people with pre-existing medical conditions, putting aside divisions over a more ambitious push for “Medicare for all” in favor of shoring up existing law.

headline.main: Democrats Unite to Begin Push to Protect Pre-Existing Condition Coverage
headline.print_headline: Democrats Rally Around Efforts to Patch Up a Fraying Federal Health Law

docs.abstract: The House-Senate conference committee that has three weeks to strike a border security deal is dominated by lawmakers experienced in bipartisan compromise.
docs.snippet: The House-Senate conference committee that has three weeks to strike a border security deal is dominated by lawmakers experienced in bipartisan compromise.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The fate of President Trump’s $5.7 billion demand for a border wall is now in the hands of a 17-member bipartisan panel that includes some of the most senior members of Congress and, perhaps more tellingly, lacks the most vocal immigration hard-liners on Capitol Hill.

headline.main: Dealmakers Dominate Panel Tasked to Reach Border Security Agreement
headline.print_headline: Job of Bridging Gap Goes To a Team of Dealmakers

docs.abstract: At a rally in Texas, President Trump insisted that crime had fallen in El Paso because of a border wall. The data and the city’s Republican mayor disagree with him.
docs.snippet: At a rally in Texas, President Trump insisted that crime had fallen in El Paso because of a border wall. The data and the city’s Republican mayor disagree with him.
docs.lead_paragraph: Mr. Trump is repeating his widely debunked claim made in his State of the Union address that El Paso transformed from “one of the most dangerous cities” into one of the safest cities in the United States after the construction of barriers at the border.

headline.main: Trump Repeats False Claim About El Paso Crime, This Time in El Paso
headline.print_headline: False Claim On El Paso, Repeated In El Paso

docs.abstract: Representative Sean P. Duffy’s proposal, which has alarmed business groups and which is unlikely to pass Congress, would also give the president sweeping powers to make trade deals.

docs.abstract: While flashy liberal freshmen soak up the attention, more moderate Democrats who won G.O.P. districts in November are searching for compromise to end the shutdown.
docs.snippet: While flashy liberal freshmen soak up the attention, more moderate Democrats who won G.O.P. districts in November are searching for compromise to end the shutdown.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the most diverse freshman class in history settles into the House of Representatives, newcomers like Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez of New York and Rashida Tlaib of Michigan have been racking up social media followers and soaking up the spotlight, liberal firebrands largely elected to safe Democratic seats.

headline.main: Shutdown Prompts Centrist Freshman Democrats to Flex Their Muscles
headline.print_headline: Centrists Aim To Make Mark As Democrats

docs.abstract: Members of Congress say consumers often suffer when makers of brand-name drugs manipulate patents to stave off competition and keep prices high.
docs.snippet: Members of Congress say consumers often suffer when makers of brand-name drugs manipulate patents to stave off competition and keep prices high.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When a pharmaceutical company sold its patent rights for a blockbuster drug to an Indian tribe 16 months ago, stymied competitors and consumer groups condemned the move as a flagrant abuse of the patent system.

headline.main: Indian Tribe Joins Big Pharma at the Supreme Court, Defending a Lucrative Deal
headline.print_headline: Lucrative Deal Between Big Pharma and Indian Tribe Faces New Scrutiny

docs.abstract: The move is intended to dissuade Central American migrants from making the long, dangerous journey through Mexico. It is expected to be challenged in court.
docs.snippet: The move is intended to dissuade Central American migrants from making the long, dangerous journey through Mexico. It is expected to be challenged in court.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration said Thursday that it would start blocking a small number of asylum seekers from entering the United States from Mexico, using the San Ysidro border crossing near San Diego as the first location to turn back immigrants applying for refugee status.

headline.main: U.S. to Begin Blocking Asylum Seekers From Entering Over Mexican Border
headline.print_headline: U.S. Will Block Asylum Seekers Entering From Mexico

docs.abstract: The United States and China will meet later this month as administration officials look to calm volatile markets amid concerns an agreement may not be in reach.
docs.snippet: The United States and China will meet later this month as administration officials look to calm volatile markets amid concerns an agreement may not be in reach.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As a critical round of talks with China kicks off next week, the Trump administration is increasingly pessimistic that Beijing will make the kind of deep structural changes to its economy that the United States wants as part of a comprehensive trade agreement, according to officials involved with the talks.

headline.main: Pessimism Looms Over Prospect of a Sweeping China Trade Deal
headline.print_headline: As China Trade Talks Near, Few U.S. Officials Expect a Sweeping Deal
